**Inner classes** = classes defined **inside another class** when they are closely related.
They can access the outer classâ€™s properties and methods.

**Example:**

```kotlin
class ListView(val items: Array<String>) {
    inner class ListViewItem {
        fun displayItem(position: Int) {
            println(items[position]) // can use outer class's 'items'
        }
    }
}

val listView = ListView(arrayOf("Name1", "Name2", "Name3", "Name4"))
listView.ListViewItem().displayItem(2) // prints "Name3"
```
